The paper proposes a new approach for object recognition using a passive meta-neural network that analyzes acoustic scattering. This falls under the category of signal processing and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), as the paper focuses on analyzing acoustic scattering. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the proposed mechanism has potential applications in smart transducers that automatically analyze signals. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new approach for deep learning. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the proposed approach can be applied to object recognition. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the proposed approach involves analyzing acoustic signals.
